cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.SY, cs.OS, cs.PL

This paper focuses on the analysis of patched vulnerabilities in the Android operating system, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The study also involves analyzing the affected layers and OS versions, which relates to software engineering (cs.SE) and operating systems (cs.OS). The delay in patching vulnerabilities and inconsistencies among public vulnerability data sources also involve system-level issues, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the study involves analyzing the timeline of each vulnerability, which relates to programming languages (cs.PL) and software development.
